    <div class="container">

        <div class="row heading">
                <div class="col-md-6 main_header"><img class="img-responsive img-rounded" src="{% static 'enpredict/images/EnP_nastrone1.png' %}" alt="">

<h2><small> Enhancers' Prediction Database</small></h2>
                <p>Service <b>EnPredict</b> was created in order to publish the results of enhancers prediction in <i>Drosophila melanogaster</i> and <i> Homo sapiens</i> genomes and contains tools:</p><ul>
                <li><b>Compute prediction</b> - dynamically computing prediction of enhancers</li>
                <li><b>Mutate</b> - searching for the best point mutations for inactivating enhancer</li></ul>

            </div></div>
        </div>
        <hr>

        <div class="row my_content" >
            <div id="classifiers" style="display: inline;" class="col-md-3">
                <h2>Classifiers</h2>
                <p>Classifiers used for computing prediction value of being an enhancer was based on Random Forest method. Attributes were frequency of 4-mers in sequence (e.g. AATC). Training data for <i>D. melanogaster</i> genome was taken from <a href="http://redfly.ccr.buffalo.edu/">REDFly</a>, and for <i>H. sapiens</i> genome were taken from <a href="http://enhancer.lbl.gov/">VISTA Enhancer browser</a>.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="resources" style="display: inline;" class="col-md-3">
                <h2>Resources</h2>
                <p>Results of the classification were split into 2 sets. Division criteria were: thedatabase on which classificators were trained and frames and steps length: for Drosophila melanogaster genome: <a href="http://redfly.ccr.buffalo.edu/">REDFly</a> (200 n./ 100 n.), and for Human genome: <a href="http://enhancer.lbl.gov/">VISTA</a> (1500 n./ 750 n.). Our results can be exported to the <a href="https://genome.ucsc.edu/">UCSC Genome Browser</a> or all data can be downloaded in WIG file format.</p>
            </div>
            <div id="compute" style="display: inline;" class="col-md-3">
                <h2>Compute prediction</h2>
                <p>This tool is used to compute the prediction of being an enhancer. It uses classifiers based on Random Forest method, trained on 4-mers frequency of DNA sequence. Results of prediction are visualized by an interactive graphic containing line charts using the library <a href="http://bokeh.pydata.org/en/latest/">Bokeh</a></p>
<input type="button" class="btn btn-default" id="info_compute_prediction_btn" onclick="clickInfoComputePrediction()" value="See Manual"></input> or Download: <a href="{% static 'enpredict/media/EnPredict_manual.pdf' %}" download><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-download"></span></a>
            </div>
            <div id="mutate" style="display: inline;" class="col-md-3">
                <h2>Mutate</h2>
                <p>This tool is used to find a point mutations which decreases prediction value of the DNA sequence to the level of potentially enhancer inactivating. It uses classifiers based on Random Forest method, trained on 4-mers frequency of DNA sequence. </p>
<input type="button" class="btn btn-default" id="info_mutate_btn" onclick="clickInfoMutate()" value="Manual"></input> or Download: <a href="{% static 'enpredict/media/EnPredict_manual.pdf' %}" download><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-download"></span></a>
            </div>

</div>
